A ð1:5þ Þ-Approximation Algorithm for
Unsigned Translocation Distance
Yun Cui, Lusheng Wang, Daming Zhu, and Xiaowen Liu
Abstract—Genome rearrangement is an important area in computational biology and bioinformatics. The translocation operation
is one of the popular operations for genome rearrangement. It was proved that computing the unsigned translocation distance is
NP-hard. In this paper, we present a ð1:5þ Þ-approximation algorithm for computing the unsigned translocation distance that
improves upon the best known 1.75-ratio. The runtime of our algorithm is Oðn2 þ ð4Þ1:5
ffiffiffiffiffiffiffiffiffiffiffiffi
logð4Þ
