5.3 Important Inequalities
Let zin be the number of isolated 2-cycles in minSPs in
G5sðA;BÞ and zout be the number of isolated 2-cycles outside
any minSP in G5sðA;BÞ. By definitions, z ¼ zþ zin þ zout.
We use the following lemma to bound zout:
Lemma 11. zout  st þ sir. (The proof is given in Appendix A.)
